# Web Frontend Flow

- Keep the frontend build-free: vanilla JS modules, no framework or npm dependency additions.
- Use `app.js` as wiring only; avoid direct cross-feature imports between UI modules.
- Read and mutate shared UI state via `state.js`; do not store source-of-truth state in DOM nodes.
- Access static DOM references through `dom.js`; avoid ad hoc element lookups in feature modules.
- Route all network calls through `web/js/modules/api.js` and handle timeout + non-OK responses.
- Prefer `textContent` for user-derived strings; use `innerHTML` only for trusted and escaped content.
